%section
  .container
    .centered-row
      %h2 Recruitment is hard
      %h4.subheader we do the work for you
    .three-width-row
      .column
        %h5 We Select
        %p You have to be amazing to study at Makers Academy. We have a tough selection process, that tests for determination and technical aptitude, and accepts less than 10% of applicants. We find exceptional people for you, and then train them.
      .column
        %h5 We Train
        %p Our students spend 10-14 hours a day, 5-7 days a week, learning to be developers. Their code is clean, maintainable and extendable. They're advocates of TDD, pair programming, SOLID and Agile principles. They've learned to build software in teams.
      .column
        %h5 We Match
        %p You get a shortlist of candidates matched (by our engineers) to your needs, based on the in-depth knowledge we have about their commercial background, technical ability, motivations and characteristics - we've spent three months with them.

%section.backgrounded
  .container
    .centered-row
      %h4.subheader How will it
      %h2 Work for you?
    .three-width-row
      .column
        %h4 1. Post a Job
        %p Complete our job description, which is tailored to the specific needs of the Makers Academy talent pool. We'll use it to create your shortlist.
      .column
        %h4 2. Meet
        %p Once we've done our matching, you can follow your usual process, whether that's a tech test, a pairing interview or drinks at your place.
      .column
        %h4 3. Hire
        %p Most of our candidates get multiple offers and are hired within a few weeks of graduating. Make an attractive offer and secure the top talent.

%section.half-slider
